        <div class="project">
            <h2>Project A_Urbanistic</h2>
            <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Redesign urban spaces in a town with a 55,000 population to create a pedestrian-friendly, liveable city center.</p>
            <p><strong>Role:</strong> Urban Planner and Project Coordinator.</p>
            <p><strong>Context:</strong> Part of a complex urban, economic, and transport strategy.</p>
            <p><strong>Process:</strong> Conducted extensive research, collaborated with a cross-professional team, developed conceptual models, and organized citizen participation events for feedback.</p>
            <p><strong>Tools and Techniques:</strong> Surveys, symposiums, participatory design methods, CAD software.</p>
            <p><strong>Challenges and Solutions:</strong> Managed diverse stakeholder needs through inclusive design processes.</p>
            <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Delivered a proposal for a pedestrian-friendly city center, enhancing urban liveability and community engagement.</p>
