            <h2>Project B_Design of Train Station</h2>
            <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Design a new train station, including public space and infrastructure, as part of the modernization of the Prague-Kladno railway.</p>
            <p><strong>Role:</strong> Architect responsible for the design of the train station and surrounding areas.</p>
            <p><strong>Context:</strong> Diplomatic project addressing urban infrastructure and public space improvement.</p>
            <p><strong>Process:</strong> Analyzed current transportation needs, created architectural plans, developed prototypes, and conducted usability testing.</p>
            <p><strong>Tools and Techniques:</strong> CAD software, architectural modeling, usability testing.</p>
            <p><strong>Challenges and Solutions:</strong> Balanced infrastructure requirements with user-centric design.</p>
            <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Designed a functional and aesthetically pleasing train station that integrates with the urban environment.</p>
            <p><a href="file:///mnt/data/Project%20B_Design%20of%20train%20station.pdf" target="_blank">View Project B PDF</a></p>
